Package: circreg
Type: Package
Title: Calculate Multiple Regression for Library Circulation Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Author: Benjamin Kon
Maintainer: "Benjamin Kon <benjaminkon@mail.usf.edu> [aut, cre]"
Description: Accepts a data frame containing bibliographic data with the following attributes:TITLE, CALL_NUMBER, TOTAL_CHARGES, PAGES, PRICE, and DATE_CREATED.
    Calculates circulation frequency of each item as the number of charges per month since the date of creation.
    Sub-divides call numbers and outputs a histogram showing average circulation frequency for broad non-fiction categories.
    Computes and outputs a multiple regression with circulation frequency as the dependent variable and number of pages, price, and age in months as independent variables.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.3)
Imports: ggplot2
License: CC0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
